# Documentation Rules

> [!NOTE]
> **Purpose:** Static rules governing how the agent maintains and modifies files in the `docs/` folder.

## 1. Keep Documents Generic (For Templates)
* **Living Documentation:** The files under `docs/` are living documents designed to be copied and customized for the target repository.
* **No Hardcoding:** Do not insert target-specific credentials, private repository tokens, database secrets, or project-specific developer details.
* **Placeholder Syntax:** Use clean, square-bracketed placeholders (e.g., `[Project Name]`, `[e.g., React, TypeScript]`) for any customizable segments.

## 2. Structural & Link Integrity
* **Link Resolution:** Any edits to document structures must verify that all cross-document markdown links (such as link references from `technical.md` to `architecture.md`) remain valid and resolve correctly.
* **Consistency:** Maintain standard markdown section headers so that automation scripts (such as dynamic learning or setup skills) can parse them cleanly.

## 3. Grounding Before Changing
* **Dependency Check:** Before modifying a document placeholder or section heading, perform a targeted non-mutating codebase search (e.g., glob/grep search) to see if onboarding scripts, skills, or rules rely on those specific structures.
